      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How many creatine gummies should a beginner take per day?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Follow the manufacturer\'s recommended serving size, which typically provides 3-5g of creatine monohydrate. Most creatine gummies contain 1-1.5g per gummy, requiring 2-4 gummies per serving. The International Society of Sports Nutrition recommends 3-5g of creatine monohydrate daily for maintenance. Some products require 4-6 gummies to reach this dose. Check the supplement facts panel carefully — the per-gummy dose varies significantly between brands. For beginners weighing under 150 lbs, 3g daily is sufficient. For those over 150 lbs, 5g is optimal.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Is creatine safe for beginners?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Creatine monohydrate is the most studied sports supplement in history, with over 500 peer-reviewed studies confirming its safety and efficacy. The International Society of Sports Nutrition published a position stand in 2017 stating that creatine monohydrate supplementation at recommended doses (3-5g daily) has no adverse effects on kidney function, liver function, or hydration status in healthy individuals. Common myths about creatine causing kidney damage, dehydration, or muscle cramps have been consistently debunked in clinical trials. The only documented side effect is a modest increase in body weight (1-3 lbs) from intracellular water retention, which is a normal and expected part of creatine\'s mechanism.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'When should beginners take creatine gummies?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Timing is less important than consistency. The primary goal is maintaining elevated muscle creatine stores through daily supplementation, regardless of when you take it. However, some research suggests a slight advantage to taking creatine immediately after exercise, when muscle blood flow and nutrient uptake are elevated. A 2013 study in the Journal of the International Society of Sports Nutrition found that post-workout creatine supplementation produced marginally greater improvements in lean mass and strength compared to pre-workout timing. For beginners, the simplest approach is to take creatine gummies at the same time every day — with breakfast, post-workout, or before bed — and prioritize consistency over optimization.' },
