    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Can women take creatine gummies?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Absolutely. Creatine is equally effective and safe for women. A growing body of research shows that women may actually benefit more from creatine supplementation relative to men, particularly for cognitive function, bone density, and mood regulation. A 2021 review in Nutrients found that creatine supplementation in women improved exercise performance, reduced mental fatigue, and supported bone health — without causing masculine bulking. Women typically start with 3g daily rather than 5g due to lower average body weight. The stigma around creatine being "only for bodybuilders" is outdated — it is now recognized as a broadly beneficial supplement for anyone engaged in resistance training, high-intensity exercise, or cognitive performance optimization.' },
    },
  ],
};
